<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-22T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-22T19:00:00-05:00" n="976" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d976">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 714.1515/45a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Ewing</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-22T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Inquire whether pending a definite arbitral boundary decision the
                            Government of Honduras would be prepared to withdraw all her troops to
                            the south and east of the Merendén mountains on condition that the
                            Government of Guatemala would likewise withdraw all her troops to the
                            north and west of the Motagua River. The zone lying between these
                            boundaries to be regarded by both Republics as neutral and neither
                            Government to have armed forces therein.</p>
                        <p>Report by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>